5px|right|upright|David Thompson is the only player in program history to have his number retired.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=NC State Wolfpack|No.|Player|Years}}\n|-\n|10||[[Nate McMillan]]||1984\u201386\n|-\n|13||[[Chris Corchiani]]||1987\u201391\n|-\n|rowspan=2|14||[[Vinny Del Negro]]||1984\u201388\n|-\n|[[Vann Williford]]||1966\u201370\n|-\n|21||[[Rodney Monroe]]||1987\u201391\n|-\n|rowspan=5|24||[[Tommy Burleson]]||1971\u201374\n|-\n|[[Tom Gugliotta]]||1988\u201392\n|-\n|[[Julius Hodge]]||2001\u201305\n|-\n|[[John Richter]]||1956\u201359\n|-\n|[[T. J. Warren]]||2012\u201314\n|-\n|rowspan=2|25||[[Monte Towe]]||1972\u201375\n|-\n|[[Dereck Whittenburg]]||1979\u201383\n|-\n|32||[[Kenny Carr]]||1974\u201377\n|-\n|35||[[Sidney Lowe]]||1979\u201383\n|-\n|41||[[Thurl Bailey]]||1979\u201383\n|-\n|43||[[Lorenzo Charles]]||1981\u201385\n|-style=\"background:#BBBBBB;\"\n|44||[[David Thompson (basketball)|David Thompson]]||1972\u201375\n|-\n|52||[[Todd Fuller]]||1992\u201396\n|-\n|70||[[Dick Dickey]]||1946\u201350\n|-\n|73||[[Vic Molodet]]||1953\u201356\n|-\n|77||[[Sam Ranzino]]||1947\u201351\n|-\n|78||[[Lou Pucillo]]||1956\u201359\n|-\n|80||[[Bobby Speight]]||1950\u201353\n|-\n|84||[[Ronnie Shavlik]]||1953\u201356\n|}\n\u2013 David Thompson's #44 is NC State's only retired number.\n\n=== All-time leaders ===\n{{Columns-start}}\n==== Points ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Rank\n!Player<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/gopack.com/documents/2019/10/28/2019_20_Media_Guide_Online_.pdf|title=NC State Hoops 2019\u201320 Media Guide|website=gopack.com|access-date=April 12, 2020|page=77}}</ref>\n!Years\n!Points\n|-\n|1.\n|{{sortname|Rodney|Monroe}}\n|1987\u201391\n|2,551\n|-\n|2.\n|{{sortname|David|Thompson|dab=basketball}} \n|1972\u201375\n|2,309\n|-\n|3. \n|{{sortname|Julius|Hodge}}\n|2001\u201305\n|2,040\n|-\n|4. \n|{{sortname|Sam|Ranzino}}\n|1993\u201397\n|1,967\n|-\n|5. \n|{{sortname|Charles|Whitney}}\n|1976\u201380\