the [[NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Championship|NCAA Tournament]] 27 times. Their combined record is 34\u201325. They were National Champions in 1974 and 1983.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=NC State Wolfpack|Year|Seed|Round|Opponent|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1950 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1950]] ||  || Elite Eight<br>Final Four<br>National 3rd Place Game || Holy Cross<br>CCNY<br>Baylor || '''W''' 87\u201374<br>L 73\u201378<br>'''W''' 53\u201341\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1951 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1951]] ||  || Sweet Sixteen<br>Elite Eight<br>Regional 3rd Place Game || Villanova<br>Illinois<br>St. John's || '''W''' 67\u201362<br>L 77\u201384<br>L 59\u201371\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1952 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1952]] ||  || Sweet Sixteen<br>Regional 3rd Place Game || St. John's<br>Penn State || L 49\u201360<br>'''W''' 69\u201360\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1954 NCAA Basketball Tournament|1954]] ||  || First Round<br>Sweet Sixteen<br>Regional 3rd Place Game || George Washington<br>La Salle<br>Cornell || '''W''' 75-73<br>L 81-88<br>'''W''' 65-54\n|- align=\"center\"\n| [[1956 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1956]] ||  || First Round || Canisius || L 78\u201379<sup>4OT</sup>\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1965 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1965]] ||  || Sweet Sixteen<br>Regional 3rd Place Game || Princeton<br>Saint Joseph's || L 48\u201366<br>'''W''' 103\u201381\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1970 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1970]] ||  || Sweet Sixteen<br>Regional 3rd Place Game || St. Bonaventure<br>Niagara || L 68\u201380<br>'''W''' 108\u201388\n|- align=\"center\" \n| [[1974 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1974]] ||  || Sweet Sixteen<br>Elite Eight<br>Final Four<br>National Championship || Providence<br>Pittsburgh<br>UCLA<br>Marquette || '''W''' 92\u201378<br>'''W''' 100\u201372<br>'''W''' 80\u201377<sup>2OT</sup><br>'''W'