am Ranzino]]||1947\u201351\n|-\n|78||[[Lou Pucillo]]||1956\u201359\n|-\n|80||[[Bobby Speight]]||1950\u201353\n|-\n|84||[[Ronnie Shavlik]]||1953\u201356\n|}\n\u2013 David Thompson's #44 is NC State's only retired number.\n\n=== All-time leaders ===\n{{Columns-start}}\n==== Points ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Rank\n!Player<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/gopack.com/documents/2019/10/28/2019_20_Media_Guide_Online_.pdf|title=NC State Hoops 2019\u201320 Media Guide|website=gopack.com|access-date=April 12, 2020|page=77}}</ref>\n!Years\n!Points\n|-\n|1.\n|{{sortname|Rodney|Monroe}}\n|1987\u201391\n|2,551\n|-\n|2.\n|{{sortname|David|Thompson|dab=basketball}} \n|1972\u201375\n|2,309\n|-\n|3. \n|{{sortname|Julius|Hodge}}\n|2001\u201305\n|2,040\n|-\n|4. \n|{{sortname|Sam|Ranzino}}\n|1993\u201397\n|1,967\n|-\n|5. \n|{{sortname|Charles|Whitney}}\n|1976\u201380\n|1,964\n|-\n|6. \n|{{sortname|Kenny|Carr}}\n|1974\u201377\n|1,772\n|-\n|7. \n|{{sortname|Ronnie|Shavlik}}\n|1953\u201356\n|1,761\n|-\n|8.\n|{{sortname|Dick|Dickey}} \n|1946\u201350\n|1,644\n|-\n|9. \n|{{sortname|Anthony|Grundy}} \n|1998\u201302\n|1,641\n|-\n|10.\n|{{sortname|Tommy|Burleson}} \n|1971\u201374\n|1,598\n|-\n|}\n{{Column}}\n\n==== Rebounds ====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Rank\n!Player<ref>''NC State Hoops 2019\u201320 Media Guide'', p. 79.</ref>\n!Years\n!Rebounds\n|-\n|1.\n|{{sortname|Ronnie|Shavlik}}\n|1953\u201356\n|1,598\n|-\n|2.\n|{{sortname|Tommy|Burleson}} \n|1971\u201374\n|1,066\n|-\n|3. \n|{{sortname|Mel|Thompson|dab=basketball}}\n|1951\u201354\n|1,063\n|-\n|4. \n|{{sortname|Bobby|Speight}}\n|1950\u201353\n|1,057\n|-\n|5. \n|{{sortname|Richard|Howell|dab=basketball}}\n|2008\u201313\n|1,055\n|-\n|6. \n|{{sortname|John|Richter}}\n|1956\u201359\n|936\n|-\n|7. \n|{{sortname|Todd|Fuller}}\n|1992\u201396\n|887\n|-\n|8.\n|{{sortname|Kenny|Inge}} \n|1997\u201301\n|833\n|-\n|9. \n|{{sortname|Tom|Gugliotta}} \n|1988\u201392\n|820\n|-\n|10.\n|{{sortname|Kevin|Thompson